<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-06-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-06-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="1550" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1550">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 312.52/636.</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">Consul <persName type="from">Alger</persName> to
                                    the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#left">No. 637.]</seg>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">American Consulate</hi>, <lb/>
                                        <hi rend="italic">Mazatlan</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-06-28">
                                        <hi rend="italic">June 28, 1915</hi></date>.</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to advise that on
                                June 26 the Municipality decreed the return of the water works to
                                the Water Company, this as a result of continuous efforts on the
                                part of this Consulate with the Governor of the State who, becoming
                                convinced of the illegality of the act, compelled the municipality
                                to revoke their action.</p>
                            <p>This will probably put a stop to further expropriation of property in
                                which foreign capital is invested.</p>
                            <p>I have [etc.]</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Wm. E. Alger.</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>